Title: To Be in Nature Now
---
A solitary sojourn in the country is, especially at this moment, only half
real, because the sense of harmlessness in being with nature is lost to
us. The influence on us of nature's quiet, insistent presence is, from the
start, overwhelmed by our knowledge of the unspeakable human fate that,
night and day, irrevocably unfolds.
